Author-Name: Arul Mishra 
Author-Name: Dhananjay Nayakankuppam 
Title: Consistency and Validity Issues in Consumer Judgments 
Abstract:
 Prior research has traced poor judgment quality to poor calibration. We
 suggest inconsistency to be another reason for poor judgment
 quality-utilizing different models on different occasions resulting in
 increased wandering in judgments. We demonstrate differing consistency in
 the utilization of models depending upon which variable is used as a cue
 and which is used as the criterion to be predicted. This results in
 differing correlations underlying judgments between the same two
 variables, an internally inconsistent pattern. We trace this to the
 utilization of lay causal models to make predictions but with the strength
 of the causal story moderating the consistency in use of the model. (c) 2006 by JOURNAL OF CONSUMER RESEARCH, Inc.. 
