Author-Name: Durairaj Maheswaran 
Author-Name: Cathy Yi Chen 
Title: Nation Equity: Incidental Emotions in Country-of-Origin Effects 
Abstract:
 Different from past research on country-of-origin effects that has focused
 on cognitive factors, this article examines the impact of incidental
 emotions and cognitive appraisals associated with these emotions on
 country-of-origin effects. Experiment 1 compared anger and sadness and
 demonstrated that country of origin influenced evaluations only in the
 angry (vs. sad) condition where human (vs. situation) control was high.
 Experiment 2 further identified the effects of agency control using a
 different emotion, frustration. Based on these observations, this article
 suggests that, like brands, countries also have equity associated with
 them, termed "nation equity," that has both performance and emotional
 components. (c) 2006 by JOURNAL OF CONSUMER RESEARCH, Inc.. 
